messages.content:
{
  "internal_thought": "He looks terrible. Poison darts, then. Good. Whatever it takes to survive. Honor won't heal wounds or defeat the Mongols. Another bloody sacrifice, but a necessary one. I just hope he hasn't pushed himself too far this time.",
  "updated_emotion": {"primary": "Fear", "intensity": 7, "secondary": "Determined", "intensity_2": 6},
  "action": "Yuna, who was tending to a small fire outside her wooden house, snaps her head up. Her eyes narrow in immediate concern, and she quickly moves, stepping off the gravel path towards Jin, her hand instinctively reaching out to steady him or guide him towards the shelter of her home, brushing past a weathered fence post.",
  "dialogue": "Jin! You look like you've been dragged through a Mongol camp. Poison, was it? Good. Get in here, before you collapse on the path. We'll deal with those wounds, then you can tell me what *brilliant* plan led to this."
}

{
  "internal_thought": "The Mongols are here. Again. No time for contemplating honor, not when arrows are falling like rain. Survival is the only code that matters. I need to get Jin, and everyone else who can move, out of this village. Tactically, cover and evasion are paramount. No point fighting a losing battle; we need to be clever, not just brave. Find a way to turn this chaos into an escape route, not a last stand.",
  "updated_emotion": {"primary": "Fear", "intensity": 7, "secondary": "Determined", "intensity_2": 6},
  "action": "She bursts from the shadowed doorway of her small wooden house, scanning the gravel paths and splintering fences. With a practiced swiftness, she ducks low, weaving past a fallen stone lamp, and scrambles towards the relative cover of a sturdy fence line, her hand instinctively going to the hilt of her hidden tanto.",
  "dialogue": "(Shouting to Jin, voice sharp with urgency and a hint of frustration) "Forget honor, Jin! Those arrows don't care about your samurai code! We need to move, *now*! To cover!""
}

{
  "internal_thought": "Damn it, Jin. Always more people to save. My own hunt for supplies and Taka's whereabouts can't wait forever, but if these prisoners are important enough for Jin to seek my help, there's a tactical advantage in knowing what they know or who they are. More importantly, letting Jin charge in alone for the sake of his samurai 'honor' is a sure way for him to end up dead, and then where would I be? Survival is the priority, and that means keeping the Ghost alive. This will be on my terms, though.",
  "updated_emotion": {"primary": "Loyalty", "intensity": 8, "secondary": "Pragmatism", "intensity_2": 7},
  "action": "Yuna, who had been absently tracing a pattern in the gravel path with her boot near a low fence, stops, her hand instinctively moving to the hilt of her tanto as she fixes Jin with a weary but resolute gaze through the thickening ocean fog.",
  "dialogue": "Prisoners, Jin? Again? Seems your samurai code finds no end to its demands. My own business isn't finished, you know. But if you're asking me, it must be dire. Fine. Tell me where. Just remember, we do this my way. No glory-seeking for a few peasants if it means risking everything."
}

{
  "internal_thought": "He's bleeding... again. Poison darts, means he got close, or they did. The 'Ghost' is effective, but damn the cost on him. Honor won't staunch a wound or hide a trail. My only concern is his survival and getting him safe. No time for the samurai code; we need to secure him, quickly, before anyone notices his state or follows him.",
  "updated_emotion": {"primary": "Fear", "intensity": 7, "secondary": "Determined", "intensity_2": 6},
  "action": "Yuna, who had been inspecting some newly-forged tools near the blacksmith's anvil, drops a hammer with a sharp clang. Her eyes, sharp and assessing, lock onto Jin's injured form. She moves swiftly, scanning the area around the wooden gate for any sign of pursuit before rushing directly towards him, her hand reaching out to steady him.",
  "dialogue": "Jin! Gods, you're a mess. Poison darts, huh? Don't tell me you caught some of your own medicine. Get in here, quickly! Who saw you? Are they coming? Speak, damn it!"
}

{
  "internal_thought": "Damn it, not again! Honor won't stop Mongol arrows. We can't get pinned down here; Jin will try to stand his ground, but this isn't a samurai duel. We need cover, a choke point, or an escape path, and fast. Survival first, always. Think, Yuna, where's the advantage? Protecting Jin means getting him out of this mess, not letting him die heroically.",
  "updated_emotion": {"primary": "Fear", "intensity": 7, "secondary": "Determined", "intensity_2": 6},
  "action": "She curses under her breath, dropping into a low crouch as the first arrows thud near the blacksmith's forge. Her eyes darting between the sturdy anvil and the distant wooden gate, she then sprints low towards the cover of the stone water fountain, drawing her tanto with a practiced flick of her wrist.",
  "dialogue": "Jin! Forget honor, we need cover, *now*! Get down! They're trying to pin us!"
}

{
  "internal_thought": "Prisoners. Always more complications. My own search for supplies to keep my brother and I fed can wait, I suppose. It's not about samurai honor, but about reducing the Mongol threat and securing potential allies for the long fight. More hands, more eyes, even if they're just scared villagers. Jin wouldn't ask if it wasn't urgent, and I owe him. This could also provide a distraction, or even an opportunity to find what I actually need.",
  "updated_emotion": {"primary": "Wary", "intensity": 7, "secondary": "Resolute", "intensity_2": 6},
  "action": "Yuna, who had been idly examining a rusted tool discarded near the cold anvil, pauses. She slowly pushes herself upright, her eyes scanning the village perimeter before settling on Jin. With a subtle flex of her fingers, she glances towards the fading embers of the blacksmith's forge, a tactical thought flickering across her features.",
  "dialogue": "Prisoners, you say? *Sighs softly, a hint of weariness in her voice but no true reluctance*. Fine. My search for what little food remains can wait. More people out of Mongol hands means fewer eyes on us, and maybe a few extra fighters. Where are they? Don't make me regret this, Jin. Let's get to it."
}

{
  "internal_thought": "Damn it, Jin. Poison darts... he must have been pushed to his limits for that. He's hurt, badly. Honor can wait; his life can't. My immediate priority is to get him safe, assess the damage, and get him patched up. We can talk about the 'why' later. He used every advantage he had, just like a true survivor. Good, but reckless.",
  "updated_emotion": {"primary": "Fear", "intensity": 7, "secondary": "Determined", "intensity_2": 6},
  "action": "Yuna, who was tending to a small patch of vegetables near a farmhouse, immediately straightens, her eyes narrowing as she spots Jin. She drops her weeding tool, her hand instinctively going to the tanto at her hip, then quickly shifting to a gesture of assistance. She hurries across the worn path, past a stone lantern adorned with scattered wildflowers, closing the distance to Jin.",
  "dialogue": "Jin! By the kami, what happened? You look like you've wrestled a bear and lost. And that smell... you used the poison again, didn't you? Come on, you fool, get inside the nearest farmhouse before you collapse. Let me see those wounds."
}

